@node Introduction "Introduction to TragicWB"

@{par}@{b}Introduction to TragicWB@{ub}

@{par}As you may be aware, many non-commercial Amiga developers have
started using 8-colour icons in their distributions - often without
4-colour alternatives. Many of these icons are designed for use with the
package "Magic Workbench" (MWB), which is Shareware.

@{par}Magic Workbench icons will not display correctly unless you are
using the MWB palette and, if you use more than 8 colours on your
Workbench screen, a hack to ensure that this palette is used for pens
4-7. The MWB package contains a "palette daemon" which will do this for
you, but $20 (or whatever MWB costs these days) seems a bit much to pay
for such a hack.

@{par}In my opinion, MWB is an overpriced collection of tasteless icons
and backdrops coupled with a rather half-hearted palette hack.
@{"NewIcons" link NewIcons} offers a much better general solution to the
problem of controlling icon colours and doesn't tie you down to a
specific set of colours for your icons. NewIcons is also free. But
unfortunately NewIcons is unsuitable for use on slow machines, so there
are a lot of MWB icons out there - MUI programs in particular tend to
have MWB icons.

@{par}There are a number of free palette hacks around which are supposed
to make sure MWB icons are displayed correctly on >8-colour screens, in
the same way that MWB's "palette daemon" does. I think TragicWB is the
most complete.

@endnode


@node NewIcons "About NewIcons"

@{par}@{b}What is NewIcons?@{ub}

@{par}From NewIcons.guide:

@{lindent 4}
@{par}The @{b}NewIcons Package@{ub} is a revolutionary GUI enhancement
system for the Amiga computer. It adds many new features to the
Workbench that, we hope, will be standard in the next generation Amiga
operating system. Specifically, it allows for a palette independent icon
system whereby icons look color correct on any system, no matter what
your Workbench palette is set to.  It allows you to use icons in up to
256 colors, adds default icons for many, many file types, and works on
any Amiga with OS2.04 and up.
@{pard}

@{par}@{b}Where can I find NewIcons?@{ub}

@{lindent 8}@{pari -8}
@{par}ftp     ftp.wustl.de:/pub/aminet/util/wb/NewIcons.lha
@{line}(or from most Aminet mirrors)
@{pard}

