@node Requirements "What you need to run TragicWB"

@{par}@{b}What you need to run TragicWB@{ub}

@{lindent 2}@{pari -2}
@{par}1. OS 3.0
@{par}2. Workbench with more than 8 colours normally
@{par}3. A hard drive
@{pard}

@{par}If you don't have (1) and (2), you don't need TragicWB, so just
delete this archive now. If you don't have a hard drive, you will
probably have a lot of fun with the Installer. ;-)

@endnode


@node Features "Features of TragicWB"

@{par}@{b}Features@{ub}

@{lindent 2}@{pari -2}
@{par}· Unlike some other palette hacks, TragicWB does not require you
to enter the desired palette values. Since it is meant for use with MWB
icons, it will always set pens 4-7 to the MWB palette.
@{par}· Every time you re-open the Workbench screen, the pens will be
set correctly again.
@{par}· TragicWB can also grab the standard NewIcons pens in advance,
so all standard NewIcons will look right even if you're short on pens.
@{par}· TragicWB is very small - because it has a simple function. This
also means that it doesn't have any more features for me to list.
@{pard}

@{par}@{b}To do@{ub}

@{lindent 2}@{pari -2}
@{par}· Make TragicWB removable - if anyone wants this.
@{pard}

@endnode


@node History "Version history of TragicWB"

@{par}@{b}version 1.0 (22.9.96)@{ub}

@{lindent 4}@{par}First public release.@{pard}

@{par}@{b}version 1.1 (11.1.97)@{ub}

@{lindent 4}@{par}Not released.@{pard}

@{par}@{b}version 1.2 (8.8.97)@{ub}

@{lindent 6}@{pari -2}
@{par}· TragicWB used to watch for the Workbench allocating the last 4
pens in the palette. When the Workbench screen was set to 16 colours, the
last 4 pens were actually the sprite colours (pens 16-19), so TragicWB
wouldn't work correctly. This has been fixed.

@{par}· Earlier versions of TragicWB could easily fail to notice when
the Workbench screen was closed, so they wouldn't obtain the necessary
pens again. This version uses a new method to detect when the Workbench
screen closes, which should always work.

@{par}· The new command-line option NIDEPTH=NEWICONDEPTH can be used to
specify the minimum screen depth at which TragicWB tries to obtain
pens for the standard NewIcons colours in addition to the MagicWB pens.
If this option is not used, it will never try to obtain them.

@{par}· If TragicWB cannot obtain the MagicWB pens at startup, it will
attempt to close and re-open the Workbench screen and then try again.

@{pard}

@endnode


@node Installation "Installing TragicWB"

@{par}To install TragicWB on your system, open the icon "Install
TragicWB" and follow the prompts. Help is available at each stage of the
installation.

@{par}When you are asked whether to run TragicWB at boot time, you
should always answer Yes. If you run TragicWB at a later point, one or
more of the pens it requires (pens 4-7) may already have been allocated
by another program. In this case, it will try to close and re-open the
Workbench screen. If you have application windows open on the Workbench
screen, this won't work, so MWB icons will still look wrong.

@endnode


